cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM. 

The paper deals with a computer vision problem of object orientation estimation using deep convolutional neural networks. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes and compares different approaches for continuous orientation prediction, which involves optimization and machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also deals with a task related to robotics (object orientation estimation), making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on vehicle and pedestrian orientation estimation tasks, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM), making it a possible sub-category as well.
